TITLE: Wife of Grant Wahl, American journalist who died at World Cup, reveals cause of death
SUMMARY: Dr. Celine Gounder, wife of deceased soccer journalist Grant Wahl, has made public the cause of her husband's death.

TITLE: Idaho murders: Coroner weighs in on toxicology reports, describes her role in case
SUMMARY: Toxicology reports for four slain University of Idaho students are unlikely to offer any new clues in the unsolved murders, the local coroner told Fox News Digital.

TITLE: Alabama women convicted of misdemeanor crimes for feeding, trapping stray cats
SUMMARY: Two Alabama women have been convicted for feeding and trapping stray cats. The women have been sentenced to two years of unsupervised probation and fined $100.

TITLE: Chris Rock compares Chris Farley to Michael Jordan, calls late comedian 'unhateable'
SUMMARY: It has been almost 25 years since Chris Farley passed away from a drug overdose and Chris Rock is comparing the comedian to athlete Michael Jordan in a new podcast with David Spade and Dana Carvey.

TITLE: How to prevent phone scams against older loved ones
SUMMARY: Kurt Knutsson, the "CyberGuy," explains how elderly people can be scammed over the phone, and the steps they can take to stay safe from telephone scammers.

TITLE: Biden grilled for claiming restaurants kick people out ‘for being gay’
SUMMARY: Joe Biden faced criticism on social media for seeming to suggest there is a mass occurrence of gay people being thrown out of restaurants across the United States.

TITLE: Extreme weather hazards continue to impact millions nationwide
SUMMARY: Extreme weather hazards are set to impact tens of millions of Americans across the country, with blowing snow impacting travel conditions in the Plains and Midwest.

TITLE: Son of Atlanta grandma murdered in her home issues stark warning: 'None of us are as safe as we think'
SUMMARY: The son of murdered Atlanta grandmother, Eleanor Bowles, warned crime is 'happening everywhere' after finding his mother's body in her garage in Buckhead

TITLE: Mississippi set to execute man for killing 16-year-old girl
SUMMARY: Mississippi is set to execute a man that pleaded guilty to raping and killing a 16-year old girl after the teen stated she would never want to be a Marine.

TITLE: Police raid European Parliament as investigators probe Qatar bribery allegations
SUMMARY: European Parliament has been the scene of multiple raids by Belgian police investigating alleged corruption and bribery related to the Qatari government.
